ouring rain","kjv_def":"water.","pos":"masculine noun, verb","usage":"water(1x)"},"H2223":{"id":"H2223","lemma":"זַרְזִיר","translit":"zarzîyr","pron":"zar-zeer'","derivation":"by reduplication from H2115 (זוּר);","strongs_def":"properly, tightly girt, i.e. probably a racer, or some fleet animal (as being slender in the waist)","kjv_def":"[phrase] greyhound.","pos":"masculine noun","usage":"greyhound(1x)"},"H2224":{"id":"H2224","lemma":"זָרַח","translit":"zârach","pron":"zaw-rakh'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"properly, to irradiate (or shoot forth beams), i.e. to rise (as the sun); specifically, to appear (as a symptom of leprosy)","kjv_def":"arise, rise (up), as soon as it is up.","pos":"verb","usage":"arise(8x), rise(6x), shine(1x), up(1x)"},"H2225":{"id":"H2225","lemma":"זֶרַח","translit":"zerach","pron":"zeh'-rakh","derivation":"from H2224 (זָרַח);","strongs_def":"a rising of light","kjv_def":"rising."},"H2226":{"id":"H2226","lemma":"זֶרַח","translit":"Zerach","pron":"zeh'-rakh","derivation":"the same as H2225 (זֶרַח);","strongs_def":"Zerach, the name of three Israelites, also of an Idumaean and an Ethiopian prince","kjv_def":"Zarah, Zerah.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Zerah(20x), Zarah(1x)"},"H2227":{"id":"H2227","lemma":"זַרְחִי","translit":"Zarchîy","pron":"zar-khee'","derivation":"patronymically from H2226 (זֶרַח);","strongs_def":"a Zarchite or descendant of Zerach","kjv_def":"Zarchite.","pos":"masculine patrial noun","usage":"Zarhites(6x)"},"H2228":{"id":"H2228","lemma":"זְרַחְיָה","translit":"Zᵉrachyâh","pron":"zer-akh-yaw'","derivation":"from H2225 (זֶרַח) and H3050 (יָהּ); Jah has risen;","strongs_def":"Zerachjah, the name of two Israelites","kjv_def":"Zerahiah.","pos":"proper masculine noun","usage":"Zerahiah(5x)"},"H2229":{"id":"H2229","lemma":"זָרַם","translit":"zâram","pron":"zaw-ram'","derivation":"a primitive root;","strongs_def":"to gush (as water)","kjv_def":"carry away as with a flood, pour out.","pos":"verb"},"H22